Data Engineer		Thomson Reuters		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong><strong>Title:</strong> Data Engineer<br /><strong>ID:</strong> JREQ048975<br /><br /><strong>Description<br /><br /></strong>Reuters TV is a startup in the heart of the world’s largest news organization. Our mission is to reimagine video news for the modern age: combining technological innovation with editorial excellence to deliver an extraordinary experience for our users.The Data Engineer is a full time position at our New York office. You will be responsible for driving major data engineering initiatives and architectural decisions for systems that ingest, transform, organize, and expose data. As a self-starter you should be comfortable working with large, complex data sets and building production grade internal tools. You will work closely with colleagues across the business along and have regular interface with our Engineering and Data Science teams.<br />The position is based out of our Times Square headquarters where we have a small, flat team with fun, friendly and skilled coworkers.<br /><br /><strong>Role And Responsibilities<br /><br /></strong><li> Building and scaling ETL/Event processing systems that organize data and manage complex rule-sets in real-time</li><li> Architecting and maintaining a data warehouses in SQL and/or Distributed data stores</li><li> Work closely with engineers across the company to improve data quality and availability</li><li> Participate in exploratory data analysis to provide product, editorial, and marketing with an in depth understanding of the data</li><li> Build and support dashboarding, reporting, and data visualization tools</li><li> Partner with the Data Science team to support development of personalization algorithmsReuters is the largest independent international news agency in the world. Founded over 160 years ago, Reuters provides society with the news it needs to be free, prosperous and informed. Each day our 2,600 journalists in nearly 200 locations around the globe deliver unparalleled international and national news coverage with speed, impartiality and insight. Each day, Reuters News is read and seen by more than 1 billion people worldwide through multiple platforms. Reuters stays true to the letter and spirit of the Thomson Reuters Trust Principles, ensuring independence, integrity and freedom from bias.<br /></li>If you believe you can bring something special to this role, we want to hear from you. You may have a non-traditional career path, education or background. If you meet the minimum qualifications for the role, let us know in a cover letter with your application. Reuters depends on diversity of thought and you could be just what we need.<br /><br /><strong>Desired Skills And Experience<br /><br /></strong><li> Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science</li><li> 2+ years of data engineering industry experience</li><li> Comfort with UNIX / Linux systems</li><li> Fluency in Python or JVM-based languages</li><li> Experience with some or all of the following:</li><li> Columnar Data Stores (Redshift, Vertica, BigQuery, etc.)</li><li> Scheduling and workflow engines (Simple Workflow Service, Luigi, Chronos, Azkaban, etc...)</li><li> Large-scale batch or real-time data processing (EMR, Spark, Storm, Kafka, Samza, etc...)</li><li> Ability to work both independently and collaboratively within a team</li><li> Interested in news and the future of television</li><li> A sense of humor always helpsAt Thomson Reuters, we believe what we do matters. We are passionate about our work, inspired by the impact it has on our business and our customers. As a team, we believe in winning as one - collaborating to reach shared goals, and developing through challenging and meaningful experiences. With over 60,000 employees in more than 100 countries, we work flexibly across boundaries and realize innovations that help shape industries aroun